{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἄντῐκρῠς</b>, <br /> <i>adverb</i> <b>straight on, right on,</b> ἄντικρυς ἰὼν παρεκαθέζετο ἐκ δεξιᾶς he came <b>straight up</b> and.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 273b, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 1068, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.4; also εἰς τὸ ἀ. πορεύεσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 223b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>outright, openly, without disguise,</b> ὅπως ἄ. τάδ᾽ αἰνέσω[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 192; ὁ χρησμὸς ἄ. λέγει 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 128; εὔχονταί γε πλουτεῖν ἄ. [prev. author] “Pl.” 134; ἄ. ἔφη χρῆναι πλεῖν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.49; ἃ ἠδικοῦντο οὐ δηλοῦντες ἄντικρυς [prev. author] 5.30\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐδὲν ἢ ἄ. δουλείαν <b>downright</b> slavery, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.122; ἡ ἄ. ἐλευθερία [prev. author] 8.64\">Refs</a>]; οὐκ ἄ. not <b>at all,</b> οὐ διοίσοντ᾽ ἄ. τῶν Ἡρακλειδῶν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 384. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> sometimes of Time, <b>straightway,</b> συλλαβόντες ἄγουσιν ἄ. ὡς ἀποκτενοῦντες[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 13.78, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Περικειρομένη” 38, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Ax” 367a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> later, ={ἀντικρύ}, <b>opposite,</b> ἄ. εῖναι to <b>oppose,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Eudemia” 1243a37; ἄ. ἐπιέναι \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<b>against,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 3.24; καταστῆναι 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Solon” 27; κατακλιθῆναί τινος LXX.3Mac.5.16\">LXX+1st c.BC+</a>]; ἐν τῇ ἄ. πυαλίδι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “CIG” “Corpus Inscriptionum Graecarum” “Corpus Inscriptionum Graecarum” (add.)(from Cragus): with _genitive_, ἄ. Χίου NT.Act.20.15, compare “PTeb.” 395.4(2nd c.AD), etc.—Grammars  distinguish ἀντικρύ, ={ἐξ ἐναντίας}, and ἄντικρυς, ={φανερῶς, διαρρήδην},compare “Anecdota Graeca - Bekker” 408, but ἀντικρύ (which see) has both senses in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus (-κρυ(ς)) \">NT+8th c.BC+</a>] probably akin to κέρας, κάρα.)","strongNumber":"G20085","accentedUnicode":"ἄντικρυς","shortDef":"oppose","mediumDef":"oppose","stepGloss":"facing","stepTransliteration":"antikrus","count":1,"_step_Type":"word"}]}